b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe29094.htm)  [Next](sbe29096.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n[Buy this Book at\nAmazon.com](http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1421228750/internetsacredte)\n\n* * *\n\n_The Grihya Sutras, Part 1 (SBE29)_ , by Hermann Oldenberg, [1886], at sacred-\ntexts.com\n\n* * *\n\n### KHA _N_ _D_ A 3.\n\n1\\. Now after they have entered the circle\xc2\x97\n\n2 2-3. The teacher sits down with his face to the east, the others, according\nto their rank, (sit down) towards the south, with their faces to the north.\n\np. 144\n\n3\\. If that is impossible, with their faces to all directions.\n\n4\\. Let them expect the rising of the sun,\n\n5\\. And when they behold it in its splendour,\n\n6 6. Let them with (the words), 'Recite, sir!' seize with their hands, holding\nthe right hand uppermost, the feet of the teacher, which have been washed,\nwith the right (hand) the right (foot), with the left the left,\n\n7 7. And having then put (the hands) into the vessel used for the expiation,\ninto water in which pieces of Durva stalks are, let them begin their study,\nwhen their hands have ceased to drip.\n\n8\\. This is the rite. But when they are tired, let one of them bring it about\nthat the vessel used for the expiation be not empty.\n\n9\\. And all (should do so) at the beginning and the end of (each) Adhyaya.\n\n10 10. (All) that is done continuously, without interruption.\n\n11\\. Now the expiation.\n\n12 12. The syllable OM, the Mahavyah _ri_ tis, the Savitri, the Rathantara,\nthe B _ri_ hat, the Vamadevya; B _ri_ hat and Rathantara with repetition and\nKakubh-forming.\n\np. 145\n\n13 13. These (holy words and verses) are (thus) made to attain (the number of)\nten.\n\n14 14. 'Of decades consists the Vira _g_ '\xc2\x97thus says the Brahma _n_ a.\n\n* * *\n\n### Footnotes\n\n[143:2-3](sbe29095.htm#fr_330) 3, 2, 3. Comp. IV, 8, 2-4.\n\n[144:6](sbe29095.htm#fr_331) Comp. above, II, 5, 10, &c.\n\n[144:7](sbe29095.htm#fr_332) The translation of apinvamanai _h_ pa _n_ ibhi\n_h_ is conjectural. Naraya _n_ a's explanation of apinvamana by asa _m_ s _ri_\nsh _t_ a is inadmissible.\n\n[144:10](sbe29095.htm#fr_333) Naraya _n_ a explains this Sutra in the\nfollowing way. if it is impossible, for any reason, to recite the whole text,\nonly the beginning and the concluding words of each Adhyaya (see Sutra 9) are\nto be repeated; and these should be recited without interruption so as to form\none continual text.\n\n[144:12](sbe29095.htm#fr_334) Comp. above, III, 4, 5.\n\n[145:13](sbe29095.htm#fr_335) The Gayatri is one verse; the Rathantara and the\nB _ri_ hat are Pragathas which are changed in the usual way into T _ri_ _k_\nas; the Vamadevya is one T _ri_ _k_ a: thus the number of ten is obtained.\n\n[145:14](sbe29095.htm#fr_336) Kaush. Brahma _n_ a 17, 3; 19, 5.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: VI, 4](sbe29096.htm)\n\n"